briefTitle: A Study to Evaluate the Immunogenicity and Safety of Omicron Variant Vaccines in Comparison With mRNA-1273 Booster Vaccine for COVID-19
officialTitle: A Phase 2/3, Randomized, Observer-blind, Active-controlled, Multicenter Study to Evaluate the Immunogenicity and Safety of Omicron Variant Vaccines in Comparison With mRNA-1273 (Prototype) Booster Vaccine
summary: This is a 2-part study to evaluate the immunogenicity, safety, and reactogenicity of mRNA-1273.529 and mRNA-1273.214 administered as a booster dose.

primaryOutcome.measure: Part 1: Geometric Mean Concentration (GMC) of mRNA-1273.529 and mRNA-1273 Against the B.1.1.529 Strain at Day 29
